# Code owners for damo-ui
#
# Branch protection on `main` requires at least one approval from a code
# owner before any PR can merge. This is enforced only on PRs whose base
# is `main` — work on feature branches is unrestricted.
#
# How GitHub uses this file:
#   - `* @user` means @user is the default owner of every file in the repo.
#   - More specific patterns below this one override the default.
#   - Order matters: the LAST matching pattern wins.
#   - The file lives at `.github/CODEOWNERS`, `CODEOWNERS`, or
#     `docs/CODEOWNERS` — we use `.github/` to keep repo root clean.
#
# Owners can never approve their own pull request, so for the sole-maintainer
# phase the owner self-merges via the admin-merge path (branch protection
# does not include administrators).

